data.title: Fast Service, decent prices, amazing, authentic food.
data.text:
visiting from Chicago (Nov 2015),  too tired to drive from the Hampton inn to a big restaurant we decided to go here, instead of 'just a burger'.  Talk about a gem of a find.  had 2 taco dinner plate, wife did the same, came with beans of choice, rice, lettuce guac...  the tacos were AMAZING, mine were grilled chicken , and pork w/salsa verde, my wife had carnitas and chicken...    service was fast, people friendly, and the place was clean... has take out too...    delicious.

if you like hard shell tacos, you'll LOVE these, i had one of each. the soft shell was like any other, but the hard shell was homemade, crispy, held together great, and oh so crunchy.

data.title: Fantastic!
data.text:
Fantastic, authentic Mexican food.  Went there two or three times in my 2nd week of travel to Daly City, because I didn't know about it the first week.

Just catty-corner to the In 'n' Out Burger, whose drive through line is always inexplicably into Sullivan street and around the corner -- this place beats the heck out if it!

Had two excellent Carnitas/Spicy tacos - both soft and crispy - and enjoyed each pair thoroughly.  I think I preferred the crispy for the added texture.

Also had a carnitas burrito (regular) which was very good and satisfying.  Three for three!   Inexpensive, too.

Highly recommended if you're in the neighborhood, or are at the Hampton Inn about 5 blocks north.
